---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../components/SectionHeader.astro';
---
<Layout title="Privacy" description="Privacy policy for catatorres.ca — what data is collected and why.">
  <SectionHeader label="§" title="Privacy" />
  <article class="prose">
    <p>
      This is a simple site. It collects as little data as it can get away with. Here's what it does collect, and why.
    </p>

    <h3>Minimal computing</h3>
    <p>
      The site adheres, where possible, to <em>minimal computing</em> principles: static pages, low weight, minimal dependencies, and fast load times even on slow connections or older devices. The Lab demo is the deliberate exception. It depends on a language model hosted by Anthropic, but it's isolated from the rest of the site: if the demo fails, the rest stays accessible and functional.
    </p>

    <h3>Contact form submissions</h3>
    <p>
      If you send a message through the contact form, the form delivers your name, email, optional company, subject, and message to <a href="mailto:hello@catatorres.ca">hello@catatorres.ca</a>. The email lives in Catalina's Gmail inbox indefinitely, or until she deletes it. If you want your message deleted, email her with that request.
    </p>

    <h3>Lab demo submissions</h3>
    <p>
      When you run the Lab workflow suggester, the problem you describe is sent to a language model to draft a workflow, and a copy of your text and that workflow is emailed to Catalina — so she sees what visitors actually need help with. Don't put anything confidential in there. As with the contact form, that email lives in her inbox until she deletes it.
    </p>

    <h3>Rate limiting</h3>
    <p>
      The contact form and the Lab demo are rate-limited to prevent abuse. The site stores a SHA-256 hash of your IP address for 24 hours to track usage. The hash expires automatically. No personally identifiable information about your browsing is stored.
    </p>

    <h3>Analytics</h3>
    <p>
      Vercel Analytics counts page views in an aggregated, cookie-free way. Vercel Speed Insights measures how fast pages load on real visits — loading times only, no identifiers, no cookies. No tracking across sites. No Google Analytics.
    </p>

    <h3>Third parties</h3>
    <p>
      The site uses: Vercel (hosting), Resend (email delivery for the contact form), Anthropic API (powering the Lab demo), Google Fonts (Libre Bodoni, Courier Prime). Each of these has its own privacy policy. Nothing from this site is sold to anyone.
    </p>

    <h3>Questions</h3>
    <p>
      Email Catalina. She'll respond.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
<style>
  .prose { max-width: 680px; }
  .prose h3 { margin-top: var(--s-8); margin-bottom: var(--s-3); }
  .prose p { line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: var(--s-4); }
</style>
